"book" includes every volume, or division of a volume, and pamphlet, in
any language, and every sheet of music, map, chart or plan, separately
printed or lithographed, but does not include a periodical or newspaper;

in relation to cinematographic work, a copy of the work or a record 
embodying the recording in any part of the sound track associated 
with the film;

"musical work" means any combination of melody and harmony or either 
or them, printed, reduced to writing or otherwise graphically produced or 
reproduced;

"newspapers" means any printed periodical work containing  public news 
or comments on public news published in conformity with the provisions of 
sections 5, 6, 7 and 8 of the Press and Publication Ordinance, 1960;

"Pakistani work" means a literary, dramatic musical or artistic work, the 
author of which is citizen of Pakistan and includes a cinematographic work 
or record made or manufactured in Pakistan;

"photograph" includes photo-lithograph and any work produced by any 
process analogous to photography but does not include any part of a 
cinematographic work;

"public libraries" means the national library of Pakistan, Islamabad, and 
such other libraries as may be so declared by the Federal Government by 
notification in the official Gazette;

"Registrar" means the Registrar of Copyrights appointed under section 44 
and includes a Deputy Registrar of Copyrights when discharging any 
function of the Registrar;

to cause the work in so far as it consists of visual images, to be seen 
in public and, in so far as it consists of sounds, to be heard in 
public;

the Board is satisfied that the applicant is competent to produce and publish 
a correct translation of the work and possesses the means to pay to the 
owner of the copyright the royalties payable to him under section;

the order may provide that the provisions of this Ordinance shall apply 
either generally or in relation to such classes of works or such classes of 
cases as may be specified in the order;

the order may provide that the term of copyright in Pakistan shall not 
exceed that conferred by the law of the foreign country to which the order 
relates;

the order may provide that the provisions of this Ordinance as to delivery 
of copies of books to public libraries shall not apply to works first 
published in such foreign country except so far as is provided by the order;

in applying the provisions of this Ordinance as to ownership of copyright 
the order may make such modification as appears necessary, having regard 
to the law of the foreign country;

the reproduction of a literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work for the 
propose of a judicial proceeding or for the purpose of a report of a  judicial 
proceeding;

the reproduction of any literary, dramatic, or musical work in the certified 
copy made or supplied in accordance with any law for the time being in 
force;

explanation:
In the case of a work of joint authorship references in this 
clause to passages from works shall include references to passages or by 
any one or more of those authors in collaboration with any other person;

