the performance of a literary, dramatic or musical work by an amateur club 
or society, if the performance is given to a non-paying audience, or for the 
benefit of a religious, charitable or educational institution;

the making or publishing of a painting, drawing, engraving or photograph 
or a sculpture or other artistic work if such work is permanently situate in a 
public place or and premises to which the public has access;

any other artistic work, if such inclusion is only by way of 
background or is otherwise incidental to the principal matters 
represented in the work;

the use by the author of an artistic work, where the author of such work is 
not the owner of the copyright therein, of any mould, cast, sketch, plan, 
model or study made by him for the purpose of the work; 
Provided that he does not thereby repeat or imitate the main design of the 
